          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Three Ge(Li) detectors are used with active",
                "volumes of 80 cm**3 (Philips),100 cm**3 (Philips) and",
                "95 cm**3 (Seforad) and with resolutions of 1.8,2.1 and",
                "1.9 keV at Eg=1.33 MeV,respectively.",
                "In addition a large-angle Compton-suppression spectro-",
                "meter (LACSS) is used to determine the detailed decay",
                "schemes of the Ep=1757 and 1763 keV resonances.The",
                "LACSS consists of a 90 cm**3 GAMMA-X Ge detector placed",
                "in a NaI Compton suppression shield.An extra 2 cm lead",
                "shielding reduces the standard solid angle of 120 msr",
                "to 45 msr.All detectors were shielded with 5 mm Pb",
                "absorbers to reduce the low-energy gamma-ray flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets have been produced by implantation of nat.",
                "argon gas in tantalum backings at different Ar+ energ.",
                "and charge densities (ranging from 0.15 to 15 C/cm3)",
                "The 38Ar target thickness is about 1.5 keV"
              ]
            }
